01:00:05.440 --> 01:00:17.300
I'm not certain actually how it's pronounced, but it basically does, you know, additional rounds of optimizing your in-context learning and prompting in general.

01:00:18.900 --> 01:00:22.040
you know, having access to that structure might be very helpful for it.

01:00:22.400 --> 01:00:23.440
Who knows, right?

01:00:23.460 --> 01:00:26.420
I think that there's a lot of interesting opportunities in this space

01:00:26.960 --> 01:00:30.560
where we maintain this structure,

01:00:31.760 --> 01:00:33.320
we're able to reflect on it,

01:00:33.960 --> 01:00:35.400
and then use that, you know,

01:00:35.560 --> 01:00:38.420
for whatever sort of interaction we have with other systems.

01:00:39.420 --> 01:00:41.920
And fundamentally, that's what this supports,

01:00:42.500 --> 01:00:44.540
because you have access to those Python structures,

01:00:45.220 --> 01:00:46.779
you can figure out what that's supposed to be

01:00:47.240 --> 01:00:49.000
before you go and send it off to somewhere else.

01:00:50.720 --> 01:00:53.220
So what does that mean in terms of capabilities?

